{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2253bf2d-00b5-42c1-9724-4bde3299f8dc","content":"`.testsettings` files are **not supported** in modern MSTest/VSTest — they're silently ignored. You need to migrate to a `.runsettings` file. Here's what your file contains and how each setting maps:\n\n| `.testsettings` setting | `.runsettings` equivalent |\n|---|---|\n| `TestTimeout = 30000` | `<MSTest><TestTimeout>30000</TestTimeout></MSTest>` |\n| Code coverage data collector | `<DataCollectors>` with `CodeCoverage` friendly name |\n| `AssemblyResolution / useLoadContext` | Default in .NET — no migration needed |\n\nLet me create the `.runsettings` file and wire it up:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_Sf6v9REK4XpoRjMao595Nj","name":"create","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-7b2824a0cad44b32982e912ac622ab3e/local.runsettings","file_text":"<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"utf-8\"?>\n<RunSettings>\n  <RunConfiguration>\n    <TestSessionTimeout>300000</TestSessionTimeout>\n  </RunConfiguration>\n\n  <MSTest>\n    <TestTimeout>30000</TestTimeout>\n  </MSTest>\n\n  <DataCollectionRunSettings>\n    <DataCollectors>\n      <DataCollector friendlyName=\"Code Coverage\"\n        uri=\"datacollector://Microsoft/CodeCoverage/2.0\"\n        assemblyQualifiedName=\"Microsoft.VisualStudio.TraceCollector.dll\">\n        <Configuration>\n          <CodeCoverage />\n        </Configuration>\n      </DataCollector>\n    </DataCollectors>\n  </DataCollectionRunSettings>\n</RunSettings>\n"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"create a new file at /tmp/sv-7b2824a0cad44b32982e912ac622ab3e/local.runsettings."},{"toolCallId":"tooluse_AWsK7DxLlVU6tdrdCeqxPc","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-7b2824a0cad44b32982e912ac622ab3e/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n  </PropertyGroup>","new_str":"  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n    <RunSettingsFilePath>$(MSBuildProjectDirectory)\\local.runsettings</RunSettingsFilePath>\n  </PropertyGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-7b2824a0cad44b32982e912ac622ab3e/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"a7366790-efe1-4cf5-aec8-5b93df153040","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a `.testsettings` file that is no longer supported in modern MSTest/VSTest. They need to migrate to a `.runsettings` file. Let me create the equivalent `.runsettings` file and update the `.csproj` to reference it.\n\nThe `.testsettings` file has:\n1. Assembly resolution with `useLoadContext=\"true\"` - this is default behavior in modern .NET, no migration needed\n2. `TestTimeout` of 30000ms (30 seconds) - maps to `<TestTimeout>30000</TestTimeout>` in `.runsettings`\n3. Code coverage data collector - maps to the `<DataCollectors>` section in `.runsettings`\n\n\nNow I'll write out the `.runsettings` file with the test timeout and code coverage configuration, then update the project file to point to it.","outputTokens":843,"requestId":"981A:19D864:45B6D7:5AC0A7:69FFF11C"},"id":"a2df3af8-be6f-4ffe-bfea-2dcacdcfbf83","timestamp":"2026-05-10T02:44:57.372Z","parentId":"fe5edc52-9bdb-4ae8-addd-8224fd7b7f89"}
